<h1>Training & Resources</h1>
<p class="page-subtitle">Ongoing education to keep your team sharp on product knowledge, design tools, and sales strategy.</p>

<h2>New Dealer Training</h2>
<p>Every new dealer receives a structured training program delivered in-person at your showroom or virtually. Training is customized to the brands you carry and your team's experience level.</p>

<div class="card-grid">
  <div class="hub-card">
    <h3>Product Deep-Dive</h3>
    <p>Construction methods, finish options, pricing structure, lead times, and key differentiators for each brand.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="hub-card">
    <h3>Competitive Positioning</h3>
    <p>How to sell Shiloh vs. competitors, Eclipse vs. other frameless lines, and positioning across price points.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="hub-card">
    <h3>20/20 / ProKitchen Software</h3>
    <p>Hands-on catalog navigation, quoting workflows, specification best practices, and common error avoidance.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="hub-card">
    <h3>Sales Strategy</h3>
    <p>Objection handling, upselling techniques, multi-brand portfolio selling, and client presentation skills.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2>Ongoing Training Topics</h2>
<p>Pinnacle Sales conducts regular training sessions throughout the year. Request any of these for your team:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>New product launches</strong> — Door styles, finishes, hardware, and accessories as they release</li>
  <li><strong>Inset cabinetry masterclass</strong> — Shiloh's 6 inset variations, selling strategies, and specification tips</li>
  <li><strong>Eclipse frameless selling</strong> — Why frameless, how to present it, and winning the "frameless vs. face-frame" conversation</li>
  <li><strong>Custom paint program</strong> — Sherwin-Williams color matching, pricing structure, and order requirements</li>
  <li><strong>Slatted wood & specialty products</strong> — Range hoods, open shelving, end caps, and decorative panels</li>
  <li><strong>Nevara cabinetry</strong> — Product overview, target market, and how it complements Shiloh/Eclipse</li>
  <li><strong>Showroom merchandising</strong> — Display strategy, sample management, and visual selling techniques</li>
  <li><strong>Warranty & claims</strong> — Process review, documentation requirements, and how to avoid common issues</li>
</ul>

<h2>Sales Tools & Resources</h2>

<div class="card-grid">
  <div class="hub-card">
    <h3>Brand Comparison Sheets</h3>
    <p>Side-by-side feature comparisons for Shiloh, Eclipse, and Aspect to help clients choose the right line.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="hub-card">
    <h3>Pricing Quick-Reference</h3>
    <p>Multiplier sheets, upcharge lists, and custom modification pricing for fast quoting.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="hub-card">
    <h3>Finish & Material Guides</h3>
    <p>Complete catalogs of available stains, paints, wood species, laminates, and specialty finishes by brand.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="hub-card">
    <h3>Client Presentation Templates</h3>
    <p>Professional slide decks and leave-behind materials for presenting Shiloh and Eclipse to homeowners.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<h2>Request Training</h2>
<p>Ready to schedule a training session for your team? <a href="/dealer-hub/submit">Submit a request here</a>, or contact your Pinnacle Sales territory rep at <a href="mailto:marketing@pinnaclesales.biz">marketing@pinnaclesales.biz</a> with your preferred dates, topics, and whether you'd like in-person or virtual delivery.</p>

